Ondo State Governor, Rotimi Akeredolu, on Tuesday announced that he has tested positive for covid-19. “Earlier today, I got confirmation of a positive result for Covid-19. I am asymptomatic and not displaying any symptoms,” Akeredolu said in a footage on his Facebook page. I am currently self-isolating and supervised home management will be administered by the wonderful team at our Infectious Disease Hospital.’ To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .